article.headline: Robert Morris 88, Long Island U. 72
article.story: CORAOPOLIS, Pa. (AP) -- Tony Lee scored 13 points, grabbed 10 rebounds and recorded 11 assists to lead Robert Morris to an 88-72 victory over Long Island University on Saturday. A.J. Jackson and Francisco Bateko each scored 14 points for Robert Morris (19-16, 10-2 Northeast Conference) while Jeremy Chappell also had 13 points. Kellen Allen had 23 points for Long Island (12-11, 4-8), while Ron Manigualt had 13, Kyle Johnson contributed 12 and Jaytornayh Wisseh added 11. Robert Morris had a 46-28 lead at the half and held a double-digit lead throughout the second period.
